Downloading a video from the web

Freemake Video Converter allows you to save videos from YouTube to your computer in the file format of your choice.

Finding Video on the Web

  1. Browse to http://youtube.com
  2. To search for a video, type your search term in the box at the top of the page and click the magnifying glass.

Using Freemake to Download a Video File

  1. Once you've found a YouTube video you want to save, highlight the URL in the browser's location bar, right click, and select "Copy."
  2. In Freemake, click the Paste URL button at the top of the page.

Saving the Video in a Specific Format

  1. Choose the file format you want to save to, and click the corresponding button at the bottom of the window. Scroll left or right to see more buttons.

    Tip

    For information on which video formats are suitable for various uses, see the Video Files and Formats section in this guide.
  2. Select your preferred preset to determine the characteristics of the video file to be created. If you don't know which of the presets is best for you, select "Same as source."
  3. Wait while Freemake converts the video to the file format you specified. When conversion is complete, you will see the message "Conversion was completed successfully."

    Tip

    The process of converting and saving the video file may take several minutes. While Freemake is converting the file, you won't be able to proceed with any upcoming steps. Just wait until you see the message "Conversion was completed successfully."
  4. Click the Close button.
